* Node.js and npm installed on your system
* A ReactJS app created with `create-react-app` or a custom setup
* TypeScript installed globally or locally in your project

### Step 1: Create a New ExpressJS Server

Create a new file called `server.ts` in the root of your project:
```typescript
// server.ts
import express, { Request, Response } from 'express';
import path from 'path';

const app = express();
const PORT = 3001;

app.use(express.static(path.join(__dirname, '../build')));

app.get('*', (req: Request, res: Response) => {
  res.sendFile(path.join(__dirname, '../build', 'index.html'));
});

app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server started on port ${PORT}`);
});
```
